  "texts": [
    "DEXs, on the other hand, contribute to price discovery by facilitating the listing and trading of new tokens (Aspris et al., 2021).",
    "However, prices on DEXs tend to be less efficient, resulting in inconsistencies and variations across DEX platforms (Barbon & Ranaldo, 2021).",
    "This inconsistency can pose challenges for traders seeking price transparency and accurate execution.",
    "DEXs primarily support crypto-to-crypto transactions and rely on arbitrageurs to balance prices, which can lead to longer execution times and potential inefficiencies (Krishnamachari et al., 2021).",
    "However, DEXs do offer unique benefits by more efficiently allocating risk among traders with different risk preferences, resulting in distinct trading advantages."
  ],
